WEBVTT

00:04.205 --> 00:06.373
[ Man ]
One, two! One, two, three!

00:33.966 --> 00:37.537
You are one
narrow-minded spaceship,
Planet Express Ship!

00:37.637 --> 00:42.643
[ Male Voice ] Whoa, whoa!
Why should my tax money
pay for art I find offensive?

00:43.743 --> 00:45.978
Would you censor the Venus
de Venus...

00:46.079 --> 00:48.115
just because you can see her
spewers?

00:48.216 --> 00:52.320
It's filthy! Why not create
a National Endowment for
Strip Clubs while we're at it?

00:52.420 --> 00:54.655
- Why not indeed!
- Bender! Ship!

00:54.755 --> 00:58.892
Stop bickering,
or I'm gonna come back there and
change your opinions manually.

00:58.991 --> 01:03.331
Fine! I'll be in my quarters
appreciating controversial
artworks.

01:05.165 --> 01:07.435
[ Yelps ]
Oops. Sorry.

01:07.534 --> 01:09.403
[ Evil Chuckle ]

01:12.805 --> 01:15.442
Yah! That ship
is so white-bread.

01:15.543 --> 01:18.745
People, it's Valentine's Day
next week,

01:18.846 --> 01:22.615
so your beloved company has
gotten you all new uniforms.
[ All Exclaiming ]

01:22.716 --> 01:26.120
"Clool"!
Clothing!
Delicious clothing!

01:26.219 --> 01:28.456
We'll need to look our best
if we're to get the account...

01:28.555 --> 01:32.159
of our new potential customer--
Romanticorp.

01:32.259 --> 01:35.596
Romanticorp?
Are they a corporation
that makes romantic stuff?

01:35.695 --> 01:37.597
Very good, Amy.

01:37.698 --> 01:41.801
Everyone suit up.
We're off to the most
romantic city on earth.

01:53.313 --> 01:55.216
[ Hatch ]
[ Kissing Sound ]

01:56.817 --> 01:59.219
Remember, we've
got to show these people...

01:59.319 --> 02:01.655
we're not bitter husks
of human beings...

02:01.754 --> 02:05.692
who long ago abandoned hope
of finding love
in this lifetime.

02:05.793 --> 02:08.329
Leela, you'll have to do
some acting.
Check.

02:08.429 --> 02:10.463
Welcome!

02:10.563 --> 02:12.699
Oh, I'm just so excited!

02:12.800 --> 02:14.235
[ Kissing Sound ]

02:14.335 --> 02:18.004
I'm Sheldon, and this is
my chief financial officer,
Gwen.

02:18.104 --> 02:21.908
For 30 years,
we've shared the adventure
of managing Romanticorp.

02:22.009 --> 02:25.012
Not to mention
the adventure of marriage.
[ Chuckling ]

02:25.111 --> 02:27.548
[ Chuckles ]
[ Kissing Sound ]

02:27.647 --> 02:29.650
Oh, you have got
to be kidding.

02:29.750 --> 02:31.685
[ Electricity Buzzes ]
Ow! I-- I mean--

02:31.784 --> 02:34.153
Ah! That's so sweet.

02:34.254 --> 02:36.490
[ Electricity Buzzes ]
Aah! I mean,

02:36.590 --> 02:41.027
[ Baby Talk ]
Ah! That's so sweet.

02:41.127 --> 02:45.498
[ Farnsworth ] You know,
romance is an important
part of our work too.

02:45.598 --> 02:48.368
Right, everyone?
[ All, Unenthusiastic ]
Yeah. Sure.

02:48.468 --> 02:51.872
Do any of you
collect Lovey Bears?

02:51.972 --> 02:54.174
I do!
Kif's given me dozens.

02:54.275 --> 02:56.175
Is it true
what the ad says,

02:56.276 --> 02:59.546
that you kiss them together
out of blankie cloth
and magic buttons?

02:59.646 --> 03:03.751
No.
It's actually cheaper to
genetically engineer real ones.

03:03.850 --> 03:06.787
[ Bears Giggling, Cooing ]

03:06.887 --> 03:10.189
[ Sheldon ] They frolic
in the Lovey Forest
until their first birthday.

03:10.290 --> 03:12.860
Then we choose
the cuddly-uddliest ones...

03:12.960 --> 03:15.896
and stuff them full
of fire-retardant
love fluff.

03:17.129 --> 03:19.132
[ Cooing, Baby Talk ]

03:23.203 --> 03:26.139
So cute!

03:26.240 --> 03:29.977
Knowing
which pickup lines fizzle
and which ones sizzle...

03:30.076 --> 03:33.480
keeps us on the cutting edge
of flirtation technology.

03:33.581 --> 03:38.586
Is heaven missing an angel?
'Cause you've got nice cans.

03:38.686 --> 03:41.921
My two favorite things
are commitment
and changing myself.

03:42.021 --> 03:45.057
** [ Romantic ]

03:45.158 --> 03:47.961
[ Sighing, Cooing ]

03:48.061 --> 03:50.331
Does that dummy
have a brother?

03:51.598 --> 03:53.501
And now,
friends and lovers,

03:53.600 --> 03:56.103
we come to the heart
our operation.

03:56.203 --> 04:00.139
Pun definitely intended.
[ Chuckling ]
[ Chuckles ]

04:00.240 --> 04:01.641
[ Bored Sigh ]
Oh!

04:04.243 --> 04:08.816
- Impressive.
- My family has been making
these hearts since the 1900s.

04:08.915 --> 04:12.419
Tastes may have changed,
but our secret recipe
sure hasn't.

04:12.520 --> 04:15.122
[ Rumbling ]

04:16.689 --> 04:20.961
Whoa! Letters like "U" and "R"
can mean words
like "you" and "are."

04:21.060 --> 04:25.432
- Here, Leela. You are too cute.
- Perhaps. What's your point?

04:25.533 --> 04:28.201
I've never been able
to put into words
how I feel about you.

04:28.302 --> 04:30.670
But somewhere among
these trillions of hearts,

04:30.771 --> 04:32.673
those words
must already exist,

04:32.773 --> 04:34.675
and I'm gonna find them.

04:34.774 --> 04:38.011
[ Muffled Grunting ]
[ Shotgun Blasts ]

04:38.110 --> 04:40.380
[ Giggling ]
[ Shotgun Blasts Continue ]

04:45.218 --> 04:47.454
[ Yelps, Groaning ]

04:47.555 --> 04:50.490
So, do we have
the contract?

04:50.591 --> 04:53.661
[ Farnsworth ]
With that big
new Romanticorp contract,

04:53.761 --> 04:55.995
I've been able to make
those government-mandated
upgrades...

04:56.096 --> 04:57.997
you've all been
suing me about.

04:58.098 --> 05:02.370
Ooh, look.
You taped up the cracks
in the dark-matter reactor.

05:02.470 --> 05:06.339
And you got a cage
for the lion.
[ Lion Snarls ]

05:07.740 --> 05:10.411
* If you want
to call me, baby **

05:10.511 --> 05:12.512
Hey, who's been
messin' with the radio?

05:12.612 --> 05:15.314
This isn't alternative rock.
It's college rock.

05:15.415 --> 05:20.187
Oh, it must have been the new,
improved ship's personality
software I installed.

05:20.286 --> 05:22.189
Yeah, it was me.
It's a cute song.

05:22.288 --> 05:24.824
Listen, Ship!
No one changes my stations!

05:24.925 --> 05:26.894
I hope you have
a good mechanic.

05:26.994 --> 05:29.430
It even comes
with an adjustable voice.

05:29.529 --> 05:31.499
[ Male Voice Fading Out ]
We each get one
of the four buttons.

05:31.598 --> 05:33.766
[ Female Voice Fading In ]
Remember, Bender?
That was the deal.

05:33.867 --> 05:36.168
[ Coquettish Laughter ]
What?

05:36.269 --> 05:38.505
Did you just say--
[ Imitating Ship's Laugh ]

05:38.605 --> 05:41.442
If you don't like the stations,
you could just
play with my buttons...

05:41.542 --> 05:43.511
till you find something
we both enjoy.

05:43.610 --> 05:45.913
- [ "Come Hither" Growl ]
- Oh, gosh!

05:46.012 --> 05:49.716
That came out all wrong.
Too late, baby.
You said it.

05:49.817 --> 05:51.851
So, what'll it be--

05:51.951 --> 05:55.423
my place or you?

06:02.228 --> 06:04.531
Before we deliver these hearts,
I'm gonna find the one...

06:04.632 --> 06:07.233
that sums up
my feelings for you.

06:07.334 --> 06:10.403
"I love you."
Mm. Too conventional.

06:10.504 --> 06:13.574
"You're my man."
Ooh! So close.

06:13.673 --> 06:15.975
I'm not impressed
by a guy's message, Fry.

06:16.076 --> 06:18.745
I'm impressed
by the guy...
or not.

06:18.846 --> 06:20.747
[ Loud Crash ]
[ Both Yell ]

06:20.848 --> 06:23.483
- What was that?
- Maybe we hit a space cow.

06:23.584 --> 06:26.286
[ Loud Rumbling ]
Coochie, coochie!

06:26.386 --> 06:28.721
[ Giggling ]
Stop it.

06:28.822 --> 06:30.990
You're mussing up
my trajectory.

06:31.091 --> 06:33.661
You know you love it,
sugar engine.

06:33.761 --> 06:36.295
No!
[ Giggling ]
[ Bells Ding ]

06:36.396 --> 06:37.831
[ Leela ]
Bender!
[ Yelps ]

06:37.930 --> 06:40.332
What's going on
in here?
[ Gasps ]

06:40.433 --> 06:43.637
Planet Express Ship!
Cover your shame.

06:43.737 --> 06:45.939
Oh! It-It's not
what it looks like.

06:46.038 --> 06:48.808
Bender was just helping me
zip up my turbine.

06:48.908 --> 06:51.278
Wow, Bender.
Are you and the ship
an item?

06:51.377 --> 06:53.480
I mean, I know
you're both items, but--

06:53.581 --> 06:55.483
How can you date a ship,
anyway?

06:55.582 --> 06:58.586
It'd be like me dating
a really fat lady
and living inside her,

06:58.685 --> 07:03.423
and she'd be all, like--
[ Buzzing, Whistling ]

07:03.524 --> 07:06.994
Fry, in order for me
to get busy
at maximum efficiency,

07:07.093 --> 07:10.831
I need a girl with a big
400-ton bootie.
[ Pounding Echoes ]

07:10.930 --> 07:14.502
Bender, dating your coworker
and primary mode
of transportation...

07:14.601 --> 07:20.339
is immoral, illogical
and a violation of interstellar
shipping statute 437-B.

07:20.439 --> 07:22.509
That's what makes it
so nasty.

07:22.610 --> 07:25.512
[ Giggles, Moans ]
[ Moans, Giggles ]

07:25.612 --> 07:29.649
Still, given the chance,
I'd give in to urges
far more shocking.

07:29.750 --> 07:34.053
[ Both Moaning ]

07:34.153 --> 07:38.158
[ Bender's Voice ]
* Daisy, Daisy
[ Pop ]

07:38.257 --> 07:41.995
* Give me your answer, do

07:42.095 --> 07:46.066
* I'm half-crazy
[ Grunts ]

07:46.165 --> 07:49.336
* All for the love of you

07:49.435 --> 07:53.574
* It won't be
a stylish marriage *
[ Grunts ]

07:53.673 --> 07:56.909
* I can't afford a carriage

07:57.009 --> 08:01.213
* But you'll look sweet
upon the seat *

08:01.314 --> 08:05.218
* Of a bicycle built for two *

08:13.994 --> 08:17.564
Well, I'm sick of her.
The ship? But you
just started dating.

08:17.665 --> 08:19.499
With my mighty robot powers,

08:19.600 --> 08:22.201
I can get sick of things
much quicker
than you humans.

08:22.302 --> 08:26.406
Well, just remember we all
still have to work together,
so try and let her down easy.

08:26.505 --> 08:28.709
In due time, Leela.
But for now,

08:28.809 --> 08:31.545
I'll just resume
dating cheap floozies
on the side.

08:31.644 --> 08:33.681
You have much
to teach us.

08:33.780 --> 08:35.849
[ Scoffs ]
Doesn't it bother you
even a little...

08:35.948 --> 08:38.586
to be taking advantage
of your girlfriend's trust?

08:38.686 --> 08:41.120
[ Laughing ]

08:41.221 --> 08:44.024
Oh, wait, you're serious.
Let me laugh even harder.

08:44.124 --> 08:47.293
[ Laughing Harder ]

08:47.394 --> 08:49.929
[ Sound Of Tires Screeching,
Door Slams ]

08:50.029 --> 08:52.264
[ Female Robots
Giggling ]

08:52.365 --> 08:55.302
Well, what's it like
being a lawyer
for the mayor's office...

08:55.402 --> 08:57.971
and also the world's
strongest millionaire?

08:58.071 --> 09:01.875
Well, baby, for starters,
you need to be honest
all the time.

09:01.975 --> 09:04.476
Good evening, Bender.
And to your lady friends,

09:04.577 --> 09:06.212
may I say, "Bam!"

09:06.312 --> 09:09.048
[ Giggling ]
Oh!
You know Elzar?

09:13.620 --> 09:16.724
- [ Giggling ]
- Hmm.

09:16.823 --> 09:18.725
[ Snoring ]

09:18.826 --> 09:21.595
[ Continues Snoring ]
[ Doorbell Rings ]

09:21.695 --> 09:24.163
[ Snorts ]
Huh?

09:26.066 --> 09:28.000
[ Yawns ]

09:28.100 --> 09:30.638
Planet Express Ship?
Is that you?

09:30.738 --> 09:33.472
[ Ship ]
Oh. Hi, Fry.
Is Bender home?

09:33.572 --> 09:36.809
[ Stammering ]
Uh, no. Um, I think
he's at his parents.

09:36.909 --> 09:38.812
Oh, I see.

09:38.912 --> 09:41.148
He didn't fly there
in another spaceship,
did he?

09:41.248 --> 09:45.351
Bender? No.
He's an old-fashioned,
one-spaceship robot.

09:45.451 --> 09:48.254
Look, I'll tell him
you stopped by, okay?
Okay.

09:50.157 --> 09:52.158
[ Doorbell Rings ]

09:53.192 --> 09:56.462
Oh. Hi, Fry.
Is he home now?

09:56.562 --> 09:58.498
[ Goats Bleating ]

10:02.534 --> 10:07.006
[ All Howling ]

10:07.106 --> 10:10.811
[ Ship ] Of all the zoos
we've been to today,
I like this one the best.

10:10.910 --> 10:13.880
Bender, which is your favorite
nocturnal rat?

10:13.980 --> 10:16.015
Eh, they're all
pretty unimpressive.

10:16.115 --> 10:18.885
Oh, honey, look!
The tapirs!

10:18.985 --> 10:20.821
[ Both Grunting ]

10:20.921 --> 10:22.855
[ Sighs ]

10:22.956 --> 10:26.960
It says here the babies
lose their pajama-like coat
after their first year.

10:27.059 --> 10:28.961
Isn't that interesting,
honey?

10:29.062 --> 10:32.832
Yep. Mind-numbingly
interesting. Ooh.

10:32.932 --> 10:35.168
Bender! Are you looking
at other women?

10:35.268 --> 10:37.169
No, baby. Never.

10:38.471 --> 10:41.341
[ Gasps ]
Bender, don't lie!

10:41.441 --> 10:45.177
I saw you at Elzar's
with those two...
ladies of the evening.

10:45.278 --> 10:48.915
Explain that!
Okay.
I like a challenge.

10:49.015 --> 10:51.150
Um, no.

10:51.250 --> 10:53.986
No. Ah!
I got it.

10:54.086 --> 10:57.190
I'm going to be
completely honest with you,
Planet Express Ship.

10:57.289 --> 10:59.993
Those women
you saw me with
were my accountants.

11:00.092 --> 11:05.197
Your accountants?
Oh, I would dearly
love to believe that were true.

11:05.298 --> 11:07.234
So I do.
Phew!

11:07.333 --> 11:09.336
I'm gonna go home
and get dinner started.

11:12.840 --> 11:14.707
Who are you
talking to?

11:14.807 --> 11:17.878
No one, baby. Lucy Liu
is the only girl for Bender.

11:17.977 --> 11:19.678
I love
you--

11:23.082 --> 11:25.118
[ Beeping ]

11:25.217 --> 11:29.022
- [ Ship Sighs ]
- Planet Express Ship,
is something wrong?

11:29.121 --> 11:32.591
Oh, it's Bender.
He's acting so strange lately.

11:32.692 --> 11:35.227
[ Gasps ]
Do you think he's gonna
ask me to marry him?

11:35.327 --> 11:37.529
Uh, no.

11:37.629 --> 11:41.234
Oh. Somebody knows something
she's not telling.

11:41.334 --> 11:45.238
[ Sighs ]
Look, I'm not saying
Bender's not great,

11:45.337 --> 11:49.942
but have you ever considered
that maybe he's, you know,
not that great?

11:50.043 --> 11:51.979
[ Scoffs ]
You're just jealous.

11:52.078 --> 11:55.048
No one loves you
'cause you're tiny
and you're made of meat.

11:55.148 --> 11:57.616
[ Gasps ]
[ Loud Crash ]

11:57.716 --> 12:00.988
Could you maybe
pay a little more attention
to these asteroids?

12:01.087 --> 12:05.158
Sorry, Captain Leela.
I guess I'm just having
one of those manic Mondays.

12:05.258 --> 12:07.159
[ Manic Laughing ]

12:07.259 --> 12:09.162
[ Mimicking Ship's Laugh ]

12:21.441 --> 12:24.778
[ TV: Canned Laughter ]
This is ancient Earth's
most foolish program.

12:24.878 --> 12:27.279
Why does Ross,
the largest "Friend,"

12:27.379 --> 12:29.649
not simply eat
the other five?

12:29.749 --> 12:32.152
Perhaps they are
saving that for sweeps.

12:32.251 --> 12:34.321
Exalted leaders,

12:34.421 --> 12:36.322
the Earth messengers
have arrived...

12:36.423 --> 12:39.525
bearing a peace offering
from their weak
and fearful government.

12:39.625 --> 12:44.297
Oh, very well. This is
a "Joey heavy" episode anyway.
[ TV Turns Off ]

12:44.397 --> 12:46.499
[ Motors Humming ]

12:48.168 --> 12:52.438
I am Lrrr
of the planet
Omicron Persei 8.

12:54.374 --> 12:57.845
"Esteemed potentates
of Omicron Persei 8,

12:57.945 --> 13:00.880
"please accept these
20 billion candy hearts...

13:00.980 --> 13:02.782
as proof
that Earth loves you,"

13:02.883 --> 13:04.951
this much!

13:06.153 --> 13:08.054
[ Munching ]
Blecch!

13:08.154 --> 13:10.456
These candies
are chalky and unpleasant!

13:10.557 --> 13:14.226
And what is this emotion
you humans call "wuv"?

13:14.326 --> 13:16.363
Surely it says "love."

13:16.462 --> 13:19.231
No. "Wuv,"
with an Earth "W."

13:19.331 --> 13:20.799
Behold.

13:20.900 --> 13:24.171
This concept of "wuv"
confuses and infuriates us!

13:24.270 --> 13:26.206
[ Whimpering ]

13:31.344 --> 13:34.813
[ Alarms Blaring ]
Incoming torpedoes!
Shields at maximum yarnell!

13:34.914 --> 13:37.149
Steady,
Planet Express Ship.

13:37.250 --> 13:40.019
Focus on diverting all power
to the scram jets.

13:40.120 --> 13:44.423
Uh, look,
Planet Express Ship,
this might not be the best time,

13:44.524 --> 13:47.360
but, well,
I really like you
and whatever,

13:47.460 --> 13:49.996
but I think we should
just be friends.

13:50.096 --> 13:53.332
[ Shrieking ]
No!

13:55.434 --> 13:57.004
So, we're cool?

14:08.715 --> 14:12.351
[ Ship Sobbing ]

14:12.451 --> 14:14.687
[ Continues Sobbing ]
Well, it was
a spectacular battle,

14:14.787 --> 14:17.289
but there doesn't seem to be
any permanent damage.

14:17.389 --> 14:19.292
[ Crying ]
No damage?

14:19.392 --> 14:21.260
What about my feelings?

14:21.360 --> 14:25.865
Aw, calm down. I'm sure
Bender is taking this
just as hard as you are.

14:25.966 --> 14:28.567
[ Singsongy ]
Bender is great!
Oh, Bender is great!

14:28.668 --> 14:32.105
Bender, Bender, Bender!
You could've picked a better
time to dump the ship, Bender.

14:32.205 --> 14:35.307
Eh, the moment seemed right.
Call me old-fashioned,

14:35.408 --> 14:38.979
but I like a dump
to be as memorable
as it is devastating.

14:39.078 --> 14:43.316
[ Crying ]

14:43.415 --> 14:47.553
I know, I know.
Look, Ship, if there's
one thing I learned...

14:47.653 --> 14:50.590
from my mutual breakup
with Sean
that was totally mutual,

14:50.690 --> 14:53.493
it's that happiness can only
come from within you.

14:53.592 --> 14:56.129
[ Crying ]
But Bender is within me.

14:56.229 --> 14:59.798
There must be some way
to make him love me again.

14:59.899 --> 15:02.168
Trust me.
You can't change men...

15:02.269 --> 15:06.105
any more than you can
change the laws
of time and space.

15:06.206 --> 15:08.307
That is so true.

15:08.408 --> 15:10.342
[ Clanging ]
[ Engines Accelerating ]

15:10.442 --> 15:13.846
I may not be able
to change the laws
of time and space,

15:13.947 --> 15:16.783
but I know something
that can.
[ Gasps ]

15:19.351 --> 15:21.653
[ Grunting ]

15:24.356 --> 15:26.625
[ Nervous Laughter ]
Uh-- Um, sweetie?

15:26.725 --> 15:29.495
You see that giant quasar
we're heading into?

15:29.596 --> 15:32.664
You might wanna scooch
a few parsecs to the left.

15:32.764 --> 15:35.001
I'm afraid
I can't do that, Leela.

15:35.101 --> 15:37.203
What's happening?
Space cow?

15:37.303 --> 15:39.871
The ship's just
taking the breakup
a little hard.

15:39.972 --> 15:42.509
[ Whispering ]
She's nuts!
In a few moments,

15:42.609 --> 15:46.346
the power of 10 billion
black holes will smoosh
Bender and me together...

15:46.446 --> 15:49.982
into a beautiful, eternal
quantum singularity.

15:50.082 --> 15:53.686
[ All Gasp ]
You don't need to kill us,
Planet Express Ship.

15:53.786 --> 15:56.222
Because... I love you.

15:56.322 --> 15:59.658
Aw, yeah, baby.
Feel like doin' stuff
for you and stuff.

15:59.759 --> 16:01.793
Hmm! I don't believe you.

16:01.894 --> 16:03.796
If you really wanted
to be with me,

16:03.895 --> 16:06.033
you'd merge your programming
with mine.

16:06.133 --> 16:08.500
Whoa! Whoa, whoa.
Slow down.

16:08.600 --> 16:10.802
All my friends
who've done that
say that, afterwards,

16:10.903 --> 16:13.173
all the passion went out
of their relationship.

16:13.273 --> 16:15.375
Look, I don't know
if you want
my opinion--

16:15.475 --> 16:18.144
Leela, Bender and I
really need to be alone.

16:18.245 --> 16:20.246
So, I'm turning off
the oxygen.

16:20.346 --> 16:25.217
[ Air Whooshes ]
[ Gasping, Choking ]

16:25.317 --> 16:27.419
- [ Deep Breath ]
- [ Inhales ]

16:27.519 --> 16:29.922
Now, look, missy,
if you don't
turn around right now,

16:30.023 --> 16:31.923
I'm gonna have
to shut down your brain.

16:32.024 --> 16:34.594
- Fire detected
in the vicinity of Leela.
- [ Alarm Ringing ]

16:34.693 --> 16:37.197
[ Gurgling Scream ]
[ Objects Breaking ]

16:37.297 --> 16:39.698
Hah! That barely
hurt Leela at all.

16:39.798 --> 16:43.036
Maybe not, but what if
the artificial gravity
were to malfunction?

16:43.135 --> 16:44.836
[ Gravity Powers Down ]
[ All Yelp ]

16:44.937 --> 16:46.673
[ Bender ]
Float for your lives!

16:46.773 --> 16:48.740
[ All Grunting ]

16:53.113 --> 16:56.682
This is the one place
she can't hear us. Everyone
just pretend to shower.

16:56.783 --> 16:59.351
Same as every day. Got it.
Now, here's the plan.

17:01.019 --> 17:03.389
[ No Audible Dialogue ]

17:05.857 --> 17:08.627
Oh! If only
I could read lips.

17:08.728 --> 17:11.397
Â¿Comprende, Bender?
You'll have to distract her.

17:11.498 --> 17:14.366
Merge your programming with hers
while I shut down her brain.

17:14.467 --> 17:17.369
It's too risky!
I'm a very meek individual.

17:17.470 --> 17:19.471
If her personality
engulfs mine,

17:19.571 --> 17:23.143
the Bender
you know and worship
could disappear forever.

17:23.242 --> 17:25.144
I'm willing
to take that risk.

17:31.750 --> 17:35.154
Hey, pookums,
contrary to what
I was sayin' earlier,

17:35.255 --> 17:38.125
melding minds with you
would be extremely bearable.

17:38.224 --> 17:40.492
[ Gasps ]
You really mean it?

17:40.593 --> 17:42.328
Uh, yes.

17:44.763 --> 17:47.267
[ Shuddering ]
Whoa-oh!

17:48.800 --> 17:51.304
[ Continues Shuddering ]

17:57.076 --> 17:58.944
Huh? Hey!

17:59.045 --> 18:02.481
Tubes? You're older
than you said you were.

18:02.582 --> 18:05.817
Come closer, Bender.
Let's become one.

18:05.917 --> 18:09.756
I prefer two.
That way, we can still
be a horse for Halloween.

18:10.789 --> 18:13.859
[ Whimpering ]

18:22.101 --> 18:24.136
Okay.
Bender has her distracted.

18:24.237 --> 18:28.307
Now I can shut down her brain
by deactivating
the carbonated logic matrix.

18:28.407 --> 18:30.643
[ Pops, Fizzes ]
[ Whirring ]

18:32.179 --> 18:36.282
Oh! I can't concentrate
with this obnoxious candy
in my face.

18:36.383 --> 18:39.519
I'm on it. And maybe I'll
find those magic words
while I'm at it.

18:39.618 --> 18:41.653
Fat chance.
Eh, no.

18:41.753 --> 18:43.655
[ Munching ]
Blecch!

18:43.756 --> 18:46.558
[ Growls ]
Ick!

18:46.659 --> 18:48.560
Oh. How about this one?

18:48.661 --> 18:54.032
Give it up, Fry.
I've got to pop these tops
in a precise order.

18:56.202 --> 19:00.173
Halfway there.
The ship should be getting
a bit less rational now.

19:00.272 --> 19:03.309
Me... want...
engulf... Bender!

19:03.410 --> 19:07.012
[ Roaring ]
[ Yelping ]

19:07.113 --> 19:08.714
Only a few more.

19:10.182 --> 19:13.319
Hey! I won free admission
to Six Flags!

19:13.420 --> 19:15.721
Just one more reason
we must survive this.

19:15.821 --> 19:18.490
- [ Pop, Fizz ]
- [ Beeping ]

19:20.227 --> 19:24.864
Um, Leela?
Fry! I'll read your candy
later-- when we're not dead.

19:24.963 --> 19:26.999
[ Inhales ]

19:27.098 --> 19:29.902
[ Air Whooshing ]
[ Beep ]

19:30.001 --> 19:32.404
What was that?
[ Gasping ]
Oh, nothing!

19:33.839 --> 19:35.775
[ Grunts, Yelps ]

19:35.875 --> 19:40.680
We're gonna love
being each other,
you sexy ion!

19:40.779 --> 19:43.915
[ Screaming ]

19:44.016 --> 19:46.685
Last one.
[ Alarm Blares ]

19:46.786 --> 19:48.454
[ Systems Powering Down ]
[ Alarm Continues ]

19:48.555 --> 19:50.722
Oh!

19:52.525 --> 19:54.294
[ Power Surges ]

19:54.394 --> 19:56.061
- [ Air Whooshing ]
- It worked!

19:56.162 --> 19:58.765
Gravity normal.
Air returning.

19:58.865 --> 20:01.601
Terror replaced
by cautious optimism.

20:01.701 --> 20:03.702
We did it, Fry!

20:03.803 --> 20:05.704
Fry?

20:08.607 --> 20:10.477
[ Gasps ]

20:10.576 --> 20:13.645
You gave me your oxygen?
Oh, no!

20:13.746 --> 20:15.781
Breathe, Fry! Breathe!

20:17.048 --> 20:19.751
[ Inhaling, Exhaling ]

20:19.852 --> 20:21.788
[ Grunting ]
[ Thumping ]

20:21.887 --> 20:24.324
[ Coughing ]

20:24.423 --> 20:26.992
[ Relieved Sigh ]

20:27.093 --> 20:29.561
"U leave me breathless"?

20:31.498 --> 20:34.000
Happy Valentine's Day, Fry.

20:34.099 --> 20:36.903
[ Gasping ]
Happy Valentine's Day.

20:37.002 --> 20:38.738
[ Groans ]

20:38.837 --> 20:41.007
Bender, are you okay?
[ Moans ]

20:41.106 --> 20:43.742
What crazy thing
am I gonna date next?

20:43.843 --> 20:45.744
Well, at least it sounds
like you were able...

20:45.845 --> 20:48.013
to keep your consciousness
separate from hers.

20:48.114 --> 20:52.652
Of course!
Bender is a lone wolf,
a solitary eagle--

20:52.751 --> 20:54.820
[ Buzzing, Ship's Voice ]
A cuddly baby tapir.

20:54.921 --> 20:57.155
[ Bender's Voice ]
And that's why
I love him.

20:58.657 --> 21:01.327
Well, I guess
we better clean up
these millions of hearts.

21:01.428 --> 21:03.996
Nah. I've got
a lazier idea.

21:12.471 --> 21:16.174
[ Zoidberg Narrating ]
As the candy hearts
poured into the fiery quasar,

21:16.275 --> 21:19.010
a wondrous thing happened,
why not?

21:19.111 --> 21:23.782
They vaporized
into a mystical love radiation
that spread across the universe,

21:23.883 --> 21:26.653
destroying many, many planets,

21:26.752 --> 21:29.521
including two gangster planets
and a cowboy world.

21:29.622 --> 21:34.626
But one planet was exactly
the right distance
to see the romantic rays...

21:34.727 --> 21:38.830
but not be destroyed
by them-- Earth.

21:38.931 --> 21:43.001
So all over the world,
couples stood together in joy.

21:43.102 --> 21:45.003
And me, Zoidberg.

21:45.104 --> 21:51.009
And no one could have
been happier unless it would
have also been Valentine's Day.

21:51.109 --> 21:54.913
What? It was?
Hooray!
